# Educational Notebook : USCRN Legacy Pairs, GHCNv4 RAW. 
# 8 golden USCRN pairs used
import requests
import tarfile
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import io

# === Settings ===
baseline_start = 1920
baseline_end = 1940
min_months = 11
start_year = 1900
end_year = 2024
smoothing_frac = 0.13

# === Step 1: Download and extract
url = "https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/pub/data/ghcn/v4/ghcnm.tavg.latest.qcu.tar.gz"
response = requests.get(url, stream=True)
tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)

# Station pairs, the magnificent 8 USCRN (HUSCRN) with more than 90 years data.
pairs = [
    ("USC00012813", "USW00063869"),
    ("USC00294426", "USW00003074"),
    ("USC00402202", "USW00063855"),
    ("USC00250030", "USW00094077"),
    ("USC00018385", "USW00073801"),
    ("USC00380764", "USW00063826"),
    ("USC00013160", "USW00063892"),
    ("USC00348501", "USW00053926")
]
station_ids = {sid for p in pairs for sid in p}

# === Step 2: Extract and grep lines
filtered_lines = []
with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
    dat_member = next(m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(".qcu.dat"))
    dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member)
    for line in dat_file:
        sid = line[0:11].decode("utf-8").strip()
        if sid in station_ids and line[15:19].decode("utf-8") == "TAVG":
            filtered_lines.append(line.decode("utf-8"))

# === Step 3: Parse temperature data
records = []
for line in filtered_lines:
    sid = line[0:11].strip()
    year = int(line[11:15])
    if year < start_year or year > end_year:
        continue
    monthly = [int(line[19 + m*8:24 + m*8]) for m in range(12)]
    monthly = [v / 100.0 if v != -9999 else None for v in monthly]
    if sum(v is not None for v in monthly) >= min_months:
        avg = np.mean([v for v in monthly if v is not None])
        records.append([year, avg, sid])

df = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])

# === Step 4: Build per-pair anomalies (with pairwise baseline subtraction)
pairwise_anomalies = []

for legacy_id, uscrn_id in pairs:
    df_legacy = df[df["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")
    df_uscrn = df[df["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")
    all_years = sorted(set(df_legacy.index).union(df_uscrn.index))
    combined = []
    for y in all_years:
        temps = []
        if y in df_legacy.index:
            temps.append(df_legacy.loc[y, "tavg"])
        if y in df_uscrn.index:
            temps.append(df_uscrn.loc[y, "tavg"])
        if temps:
            combined.append([y, np.mean(temps)])
    df_pair = pd.DataFrame(combined, columns=["year", "tavg"])
    
    # Compute pair-specific baseline
    base = df_pair[(df_pair["year"] >= baseline_start) & (df_pair["year"] <= baseline_end)]
    if not base.empty:
        baseline_mean = base["tavg"].mean()
        df_pair["anomaly"] = df_pair["tavg"] - baseline_mean
        pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair[["year", "anomaly"]])

# === Step 5: Aggregate anomalies across all pairs (after baseline subtraction)
df_all = pd.concat(pairwise_anomalies)
df_agg = df_all.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index()

# === Step 6: LOESS smoothing
loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_agg["anomaly"],
                                exog=df_agg["year"], frac=smoothing_frac)

# === Step 7: Plot (dark background, styled)
plt.style.use('dark_background')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
ax.plot(df_agg["year"], df_agg["anomaly"], label="Aggregated Anomaly", color='cyan',
        linewidth=2, marker='o', markersize=4, alpha=0.9)
ax.plot(loess[:, 0], loess[:, 1], color='cyan', linewidth=4, alpha=0.6, label="LOESS Trend")

ax.set_title("Historic USCRN Temperature Anomalies (Baseline 19201940)  GHCN RAW", fontsize=15, weight='bold')
ax.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel("Temperature Anomaly (C)", fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylim(-2, 3)
ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
ax.legend(loc="upper left", fontsize=10)

fig.text(0.01, -0.12,
         "Data Source: GHCN v4.0.1 QCU  NOAA\n"
         "Yearly averages computed from >=11 months per year.\n"
         "Anomalies computed per station pair using 19201940 baseline.\n"
         "Then averaged across all 8 pairs.\n",
         fontsize=9, color='white')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import warnings
import io
import sys
import requests
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import tarfile # Standard library

# Attempt to import Basemap
try:
    from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap
    basemap_available = True
    print("Basemap library found.")
except ImportError:
    print("Warning: Basemap library not found. Map inlay will be skipped.")
    basemap_available = False


# Suppress specific warnings if needed (optional)
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=UserWarning, module='statsmodels')
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=RuntimeWarning) # For mean of empty slice
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=FutureWarning)
# Suppress Basemap deprecation warning if present
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=DeprecationWarning, module='mpl_toolkits.basemap')


# === Settings ===
baseline_start = 2010
baseline_end = 2015
min_months = 10
start_year = 1910 # User changed this
end_year = 2024
smoothing_frac = 0.13
country_filter_prefix = "US"

# Metadata URL and filtering criteria
metadata_url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/orwell2024/GHCN-tools/main/GHCNv4_stations_with_BI_BU_orwell2022.csv"
bu_column_name = "Built_2020_10km_percent"
meta_station_id_col = "ID"
meta_lat_col = "Lat"
meta_lon_col = "Lon"

# Criteria for the LOW BU filtered series
low_bu_min = 0.1
low_bu_max = 2.0

# Criteria for the HIGH BU filtered series
high_bu_min = 10.0 # Stations > 10%

# GHCNv4 data URL
ghcn_data_url = "https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/pub/data/ghcn/v4/ghcnm.tavg.latest.qcu.tar.gz"

# Station pairs for the "H8 USCRN" series
original_pairs = [
    ("USC00012813", "USW00063869"), ("USC00294426", "USW00003074"),
    ("USC00402202", "USW00063855"), ("USC00250030", "USW00094077"),
    ("USC00018385", "USW00073801"), ("USC00380764", "USW00063826"),
    ("USC00013160", "USW00063892"), ("USC00348501", "USW00053926")
]
original_station_ids = {sid for p in original_pairs for sid in p}

# --- Step 0: Load Metadata and Filter Stations ---
df_meta_us_indexed = None
low_bu_station_ids = set(); high_bu_station_ids = set()
all_needed_ids = set(original_station_ids)
print("--- Step 0: Load Metadata and Filter Stations ---")
try:
    meta_response = requests.get(metadata_url); meta_response.raise_for_status()
    df_meta = pd.read_csv(io.StringIO(meta_response.text), sep=',', engine='python')
    required_meta_cols = [meta_station_id_col, bu_column_name, meta_lat_col, meta_lon_col]
    if not all(col in df_meta.columns for col in required_meta_cols): raise ValueError(f"Metadata missing required columns: {[c for c in required_meta_cols if c not in df_meta.columns]}")
    df_meta[meta_station_id_col] = df_meta[meta_station_id_col].astype(str)
    df_meta_us = df_meta[df_meta[meta_station_id_col].str.startswith(country_filter_prefix, na=False)].copy()
    df_meta_us[bu_column_name] = pd.to_numeric(df_meta_us[bu_column_name], errors='coerce')
    df_meta_us[meta_lat_col] = pd.to_numeric(df_meta_us[meta_lat_col], errors='coerce')
    df_meta_us[meta_lon_col] = pd.to_numeric(df_meta_us[meta_lon_col], errors='coerce')
    df_meta_us = df_meta_us.dropna(subset=[bu_column_name, meta_station_id_col, meta_lat_col, meta_lon_col])
    df_meta_us_indexed = df_meta_us.set_index(meta_station_id_col) # Store indexed version for map lookup
    low_bu_meta = df_meta_us[ (df_meta_us[bu_column_name] >= low_bu_min) & (df_meta_us[bu_column_name] <= low_bu_max) ]
    low_bu_station_ids = set(low_bu_meta[meta_station_id_col].unique())
    high_bu_meta = df_meta_us[ df_meta_us[bu_column_name] > high_bu_min ]
    high_bu_station_ids = set(high_bu_meta[meta_station_id_col].unique())
    all_needed_ids.update(low_bu_station_ids); all_needed_ids.update(high_bu_station_ids)
    print(f"Metadata processed: Low BU stations={len(low_bu_station_ids)}, High BU stations={len(high_bu_station_ids)}, Total unique stations={len(all_needed_ids)}")
except Exception as e: print(f"Metadata Error: {e}"); sys.exit("Exiting due to metadata failure.")

# --- Steps 1-3: Download, Extract, Parse GHCN Data ---
# (No changes needed here)
print("\n--- Step 1 & 2: Download, Extract, Grep GHCNv4 data ---")
filtered_lines = []; dat_member_name = "Unknown"
try:
    response = requests.get(ghcn_data_url, stream=True); response.raise_for_status(); tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)
    with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
        dat_members = [m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(".qcu.dat")]; dat_member = dat_members[0]; dat_member_name = dat_member.name
        print(f"Extracting from: {dat_member_name}"); dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member);
        for line_bytes in dat_file:
             try: line_str = line_bytes.decode("utf-8", errors='replace'); sid = line_str[0:11].strip();
             except Exception : continue
             if sid in all_needed_ids and line_str[15:19] == "TAVG": filtered_lines.append(line_str)
except Exception as e: print(f"Tar Error: {e}"); sys.exit()
print(f"Found {len(filtered_lines)} TAVG lines.")

print("\n--- Step 3: Parse temperature data ---")
records = []
for line in filtered_lines:
    try:
        sid = line[0:11].strip(); year = int(line[11:15])
        if year < start_year or year > end_year: continue
        monthly_temps = []; valid_months = 0
        for m in range(12):
            val_str = line[19 + m*8 : 24 + m*8].strip()
            if val_str and val_str != "-9999": temp = int(val_str) / 100.0; monthly_temps.append(temp); valid_months += 1
            else: monthly_temps.append(None)
        if valid_months >= min_months: yearly_avg = np.nanmean([v for v in monthly_temps if v is not None]);
        if not np.isnan(yearly_avg): records.append([year, yearly_avg, sid])
    except Exception as e: print(f"Parsing Warning: {e}")
df_raw = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])
print(f"Parsed {len(df_raw)} valid yearly averages (min_months={min_months}, start_year={start_year}).")

# --- Data Processing & Anomaly Calculation ---
h8_stations_used_final = list(original_station_ids) # Keep all original IDs for map
low_bu_stations_used_final = []; high_bu_stations_used_final = [] # Store actual IDs used
df_agg_original = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly']); df_agg_low_bu = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly']); df_agg_high_bu = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly'])
final_low_bu_station_count = 0; final_high_bu_station_count = 0

# --- Series 1: H8 USCRN ---
print(f"\n--- Step 4a/5a: H8 USCRN Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_start}-{baseline_end}) ---")
original_pairwise_anomalies = []; df_raw_original = df_raw[df_raw['station_id'].isin(original_station_ids)]
if not df_raw_original.empty:
    h8_pairs_with_baseline = 0
    for legacy_id, uscrn_id in original_pairs:
        df_legacy = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]; df_uscrn = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
        df_pair_tavg = pd.concat([df_legacy, df_uscrn], axis=1).mean(axis=1).reset_index(); df_pair_tavg.columns = ["year", "tavg"]
        base_vals = df_pair_tavg[(df_pair_tavg["year"] >= baseline_start) & (df_pair_tavg["year"] <= baseline_end)]["tavg"]
        if not base_vals.empty and base_vals.notna().any(): baseline_mean = base_vals.mean(); df_pair_tavg["anomaly"] = df_pair_tavg["tavg"] - baseline_mean; original_pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair_tavg[["year", "anomaly"]]); h8_pairs_with_baseline += 1
    if original_pairwise_anomalies: df_all_original = pd.concat(original_pairwise_anomalies); df_agg_original = df_all_original.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index(); print(f"Aggregated H8 USCRN from {h8_pairs_with_baseline} pairs.")
    else: print("Error: No H8 USCRN pairs had baseline data.")
else: print("Error: No data for H8 stations.")

# --- Series 2: LOW BU US Stations ---
print(f"\n--- Step 4b/5b/6b: LOW BU US Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_start}-{baseline_end}) ---")
df_raw_low_bu = df_raw[df_raw['station_id'].isin(low_bu_station_ids)]
low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria = []
if not df_raw_low_bu.empty:
    grouped = df_raw_low_bu.groupby('station_id'); total_years_required = end_year - start_year + 1
    for station_id, group in grouped:
        if (group['year'].nunique() == total_years_required and group['year'].min() == start_year and group['year'].max() == end_year): low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria.append(station_id)
    print(f"Found {len(low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria)} LOW BU stations meeting coverage.")
    if low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria:
        df_subset = df_raw_low_bu[df_raw_low_bu['station_id'].isin(low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria)].copy()
        baseline_data = df_subset[(df_subset['year'] >= baseline_start) & (df_subset['year'] <= baseline_end)]
        station_baselines = baseline_data.groupby('station_id')['tavg'].mean(); stations_with_baseline = station_baselines.dropna().index
        low_bu_stations_used_final = list(stations_with_baseline) # STORE FINAL LIST
        df_subset = df_subset[df_subset['station_id'].isin(stations_with_baseline)]; final_low_bu_station_count = len(low_bu_stations_used_final)
        if final_low_bu_station_count > 0:
            print(f"Calculating LOW BU anomalies for {final_low_bu_station_count} stations."); df_subset['baseline_mean'] = df_subset['station_id'].map(station_baselines); df_subset['anomaly'] = df_subset['tavg'] - df_subset['baseline_mean']
            df_agg_low_bu = df_subset.groupby('year')['anomaly'].mean().reset_index(); print(f"Aggregated LOW BU anomalies.")
        else: print(f"Warning: {len(low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria)} LOW BU stations passed coverage, but none had baseline data.")

# --- Series 3: HIGH BU US Stations ---

df_raw_high_bu = df_raw[df_raw['station_id'].isin(high_bu_station_ids)]
high_bu_stations_meeting_criteria = []
if not df_raw_high_bu.empty:
    grouped = df_raw_high_bu.groupby('station_id'); total_years_required = end_year - start_year + 1
    for station_id, group in grouped:
        if (group['year'].nunique() == total_years_required and group['year'].min() == start_year and group['year'].max() == end_year): high_bu_stations_meeting_criteria.append(station_id)
    print(f"Found {len(high_bu_stations_meeting_criteria)} HIGH BU stations meeting coverage.")
    if high_bu_stations_meeting_criteria:
        df_subset = df_raw_high_bu[df_raw_high_bu['station_id'].isin(high_bu_stations_meeting_criteria)].copy()
        baseline_data = df_subset[(df_subset['year'] >= baseline_start) & (df_subset['year'] <= baseline_end)]
        station_baselines = baseline_data.groupby('station_id')['tavg'].mean(); stations_with_baseline = station_baselines.dropna().index
        high_bu_stations_used_final = list(stations_with_baseline) # STORE FINAL LIST
        df_subset = df_subset[df_subset['station_id'].isin(stations_with_baseline)]; final_high_bu_station_count = len(high_bu_stations_used_final)
        if final_high_bu_station_count > 0:
            print(f"Calculating HIGH BU anomalies for {final_high_bu_station_count} stations."); df_subset['baseline_mean'] = df_subset['station_id'].map(station_baselines); df_subset['anomaly'] = df_subset['tavg'] - df_subset['baseline_mean']
            df_agg_high_bu = df_subset.groupby('year')['anomaly'].mean().reset_index(); print(f"Aggregated HIGH BU anomalies.")

ax.set_ylabel("Temperature Anomaly (C)", fontsize=12, color='white')
ax.tick_params(axis='x', colors='white'); ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white')

# Dynamic Y-limits
min_lim_orig = df_agg_original['anomaly'].min() if h8_plotted else np.inf; min_lim_low = df_agg_low_bu['anomaly'].min() if low_bu_plotted else np.inf; min_lim_high = df_agg_high_bu['anomaly'].min() if high_bu_plotted else np.inf
max_lim_orig = df_agg_original['anomaly'].max() if h8_plotted else -np.inf; max_lim_low = df_agg_low_bu['anomaly'].max() if low_bu_plotted else -np.inf; max_lim_high = df_agg_high_bu['anomaly'].max() if high_bu_plotted else -np.inf

else: ax.set_ylim(-2.5, 3.5)
ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3, color='gray'); ax.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.5)

# Place legend outside on the right
box = ax.get_position()
ax.set_position([box.x0, box.y0, box.width * 0.75, box.height]) # Shrink main axes width
ax.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.02, 1), borderaxespad=0., fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white') # Place legend to the right

# --- Add Basemap Inlay ---
if basemap_available and df_meta_us_indexed is not None:
    print("Adding basemap inlay...")
    try:
        # Create inset axes using example coordinates adjusted slightly
        ax_inset = fig.add_axes([0.78, 0.15, 0.20, 0.20]) # Adjusted position slightly

        # Create Basemap instance for CONUS
        m = Basemap(projection='lcc', resolution='l',
                    lat_0=39, lon_0=-96,  # Center point
                    llcrnrlon=-125, llcrnrlat=23, urcrnrlon=-65, urcrnrlat=50, # Approx CONUS corners
                    ax=ax_inset)

        m.drawcoastlines(color='0.6', linewidth=0.5)
        m.drawcountries(color='0.6', linewidth=0.5)
        m.drawstates(color='0.5', linewidth=0.5)
        m.fillcontinents(color='0.2', lake_color='0.1') # Fill land/lakes

        marker_size = 10 # Slightly larger markers for basemap clarity
        # Get coordinates and plot H8 stations
        h8_coords = df_meta_us_indexed.reindex(h8_stations_used_final).dropna(subset=[meta_lat_col, meta_lon_col])
        if not h8_coords.empty: x, y = m(h8_coords[meta_lon_col].values, h8_coords[meta_lat_col].values); m.scatter(x, y, s=marker_size, color='cyan', marker='o', alpha=0.8, zorder=5, label='H8')

        # Get coordinates and plot Low BU stations
        low_bu_coords = df_meta_us_indexed.reindex(low_bu_stations_used_final).dropna(subset=[meta_lat_col, meta_lon_col])
        if not low_bu_coords.empty: x, y = m(low_bu_coords[meta_lon_col].values, low_bu_coords[meta_lat_col].values); m.scatter(x, y, s=marker_size, color='yellow', marker='x', alpha=0.8, zorder=6, label='Low BU')

# --- Function to Load and Process GHCN Data ---
# (Code remains the same)
def load_and_process_ghcn(data_url, file_suffix, needed_ids, s_year, e_year, m_months):
    print(f"\n--- Processing: {data_url.split('/')[-1]} ---")
    df_raw = pd.DataFrame(columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"]); dat_member_name="Unknown"
    try:
        print(f"Downloading data..."); response = requests.get(data_url, stream=True, timeout=60); response.raise_for_status(); tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)
        print(f"Extracting and filtering...")
        with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
            dat_members = [m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(file_suffix)];
            if not dat_members: raise ValueError(f"No {file_suffix} file in tar.")
            dat_member = dat_members[0]; dat_member_name = dat_member.name; print(f"Extracting from: {dat_member_name}")
            dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member); filtered_lines = []
            for line_bytes in dat_file:
                 try: line_str = line_bytes.decode("utf-8", errors='replace'); sid = line_str[0:11].strip()
                 except: continue
                 if sid in needed_ids and line_str[15:19] == "TAVG": filtered_lines.append(line_str)
        print(f"Found {len(filtered_lines)} relevant TAVG lines."); print(f"Parsing temperature data ({s_year}-{e_year})...")
        records = []
        for line in filtered_lines:
            try:
                sid = line[0:11].strip(); year = int(line[11:15])
                if year < s_year or year > e_year: continue
                monthly_temps = [np.nan]*12; valid_months = 0
                for m in range(12):
                    val_str = line[19 + m*8 : 24 + m*8].strip()
                    if val_str and val_str != "-9999": temp = int(val_str) / 100.0; monthly_temps[m]=temp; valid_months += 1
                if valid_months >= m_months:
                    yearly_avg = np.nanmean(monthly_temps)
                    if not np.isnan(yearly_avg): records.append([year, yearly_avg, sid])
            except: pass
        df_raw = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])
        print(f"Parsed {len(df_raw)} valid yearly averages (min_months={m_months}).")
    except Exception as e: print(f"Data Loading/Processing Error: {e}")
    return df_raw, dat_member_name

# --- CORRECTED Function to Calculate Anomalies ---
def calculate_anomalies(df_raw_data, series_station_ids, settings_dict):
    """Calculates anomalies with RELAXED baseline AND RELAXED COVERAGE (90%).""" # DOCSTRING UPDATED
    results = { 'anomalies': {}, 'stations_used': {}, 'counts': {} }
    baseline_s = settings_dict['baseline_start']; baseline_e = settings_dict['baseline_end']
    start_y = settings_dict['start_year']; end_y = settings_dict['end_year']
    orig_pairs = settings_dict['original_pairs']

    # --- Series 1: H8 --- (Relaxed baseline)
    print(f"\nCalculating H8 USCRN Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_s}-{baseline_e})")
    h8_ids = series_station_ids['H8']; results['stations_used']['H8'] = list(h8_ids)
    original_pairwise_anomalies = []; df_raw_original = df_raw_data[df_raw_data['station_id'].isin(h8_ids)]
    h8_pairs_with_baseline_data = 0
    if not df_raw_original.empty:
        for legacy_id, uscrn_id in orig_pairs:
            df_legacy = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_uscrn = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_pair_tavg = pd.concat([df_legacy, df_uscrn], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True).reset_index()
            df_pair_tavg.columns = ["year", "tavg"]; df_pair_tavg = df_pair_tavg.dropna(subset=['tavg'])
            base_vals = df_pair_tavg[(df_pair_tavg["year"] >= baseline_s) & (df_pair_tavg["year"] <= baseline_e)]["tavg"]
            if base_vals.notna().any(): # Relaxed baseline check
                 baseline_mean = base_vals.mean()
                 df_pair_tavg["anomaly"] = df_pair_tavg["tavg"] - baseline_mean
                 original_pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair_tavg[["year", "anomaly"]])
                 h8_pairs_with_baseline_data += 1
        if original_pairwise_anomalies:
            df_all_original = pd.concat(original_pairwise_anomalies); df_agg_original = df_all_original.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index()
            results['anomalies']['H8'] = df_agg_original; results['counts']['H8'] = h8_pairs_with_baseline_data
            print(f"Aggregated H8 USCRN from {h8_pairs_with_baseline_data} pairs with valid baseline data.")
    if 'H8' not in results['anomalies']: results['anomalies']['H8'] = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly'])
    if 'H8' not in results['counts']: results['counts']['H8'] = 0

    # --- Series 2 & 3: BU --- (Relaxed coverage and baseline)
    for series_name, bu_ids in [('LowBU', series_station_ids['LowBU']), ('HighBU', series_station_ids['HighBU'])]:
        print(f"\nCalculating {series_name} US Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_s}-{baseline_e})")
        df_raw_bu = df_raw_data[df_raw_data['station_id'].isin(bu_ids)]; stations_meeting_coverage = []
        final_bu_station_count = 0; results['stations_used'][series_name] = []
        if not df_raw_bu.empty:
            grouped = df_raw_bu.groupby('station_id'); total_years_in_range = end_y - start_y + 1
            min_years_required_for_coverage = int(total_years_in_range * 0.90) # Use 90% threshold

            for station_id, group in grouped:
                 # *** RELAXED COVERAGE CHECK ***
                 if (group['year'].nunique() >= min_years_required_for_coverage and
                     group['year'].min() <= start_y + 10 and # Allow slightly later start
                     group['year'].max() >= end_y - 10):    # Allow slightly earlier end
                      stations_meeting_coverage.append(station_id)

            print(f"Found {len(stations_meeting_coverage)} {series_name} stations meeting coverage criteria (>= {min_years_required_for_coverage} years).") # Correct print message
            if stations_meeting_coverage:
                df_subset = df_raw_bu[df_raw_bu['station_id'].isin(stations_meeting_coverage)].copy()
                # Baseline check is relaxed (uses .mean() and .dropna())
                baseline_data = df_subset[(df_subset['year'] >= baseline_s) & (df_subset['year'] <= baseline_e)]
                station_baselines_mean = baseline_data.groupby('station_id')['tavg'].mean() # NaN if no data
                stations_with_baseline = station_baselines_mean.dropna().index # Select stations with a valid mean
                final_stations_used = list(stations_with_baseline)
                results['stations_used'][series_name] = final_stations_used; final_bu_station_count = len(final_stations_used)

                if final_bu_station_count > 0:
                    df_subset_final = df_subset[df_subset['station_id'].isin(final_stations_used)].copy() # Use stations that passed BOTH checks
                    print(f"Calculating {series_name} anomalies for {final_bu_station_count} stations with valid coverage AND baseline data.")
                    df_subset_final['baseline_mean'] = df_subset_final['station_id'].map(station_baselines_mean.dropna()) # Map the valid means
                    df_subset_final['anomaly'] = df_subset_final['tavg'] - df_subset_final['baseline_mean']
                    df_subset_final = df_subset_final.dropna(subset=['anomaly']) # Should not drop many if parsing is okay
                    df_agg_bu = df_subset_final.groupby('year')['anomaly'].mean().reset_index()
                    results['anomalies'][series_name] = df_agg_bu; results['counts'][series_name] = final_bu_station_count
                    print(f"Aggregated {series_name} anomalies.")
                else: print(f"Warning: {len(stations_meeting_coverage)} passed coverage, but none had valid baseline data.")
            # else: print(f"Warning: No {series_name} stations met coverage.")
        # else: print(f"Warning: No data for {series_name} stations.")
        if series_name not in results['anomalies']: results['anomalies'][series_name] = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly'])
        if series_name not in results['counts']: results['counts'][series_name] = 0
        if series_name not in results['stations_used']: results['stations_used'][series_name] = []
    return results


# --- Function to Plot Anomalies for one data type ---
def plot_anomalies(anomaly_results, data_type_label, df_meta_idx, settings_dict, filename):
    """Generates the anomaly plot with basemap for QCU or QCF and displays it."""
    print(f"\n--- Plotting {data_type_label} Anomalies ---")
    plt.style.use('dark_background'); fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 7))
    counts = anomaly_results['counts']; anomalies = anomaly_results['anomalies']; stations_used = anomaly_results['stations_used']
    plot_title = f"US GHCN {data_type_label} Anomalies (Baseline {settings_dict['baseline_start']}{settings_dict['baseline_end']})"
    title_suffix = []; any_series_plotted = False
    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors']; markers = settings_dict['plot_markers']
    linewidth_raw = settings_dict[f"{data_type_label.lower()}_linewidth_raw"]; linewidth_smooth = settings_dict[f"{data_type_label.lower()}_linewidth_smooth"]
    # Plotting loop
    for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
        df_agg = anomalies.get(series_name); count = counts.get(series_name, 0)
        if df_agg is not None and not df_agg.empty and count > 0:
            try:
                series_label_base = f"{series_name}"; series_label_count = f"N={count}"
                if series_name == 'LowBU': series_label_base = f"Low BU US ({settings_dict['low_bu_min']}-{settings_dict['low_bu_max']}%)"
                if series_name == 'HighBU': series_label_base = f"High BU US (>{settings_dict['high_bu_min']}%)"
                if series_name == 'H8': series_label_count = f"N={count} pairs"
                df_clean = df_agg.dropna(subset=['year', 'anomaly'])
                if len(df_clean) > 5:
                    loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["anomaly"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                    if loess.ndim == 2 and loess.shape[1] == 2: ax.plot(loess[:, 0], loess[:, 1], color=colors[series_name], linewidth=linewidth_smooth, alpha=0.9, label=f"{series_label_base} LOESS")
                ax.plot(df_agg["year"], df_agg["anomaly"], label=f"{series_label_base} Anomaly ({series_label_count})", color=colors[series_name], linewidth=linewidth_raw, marker=markers[series_name], markersize=3, alpha=0.7, linestyle='-' if linewidth_raw > 0 else 'None')
                any_series_plotted = True; title_suffix.append(f"{series_name} N={count}")
            except Exception as e: print(f"Plotting Error ({data_type_label} - {series_name}): {e}")
    # Axis setup
    ax.set_title(f"{plot_title} - {' | '.join(title_suffix)}", fontsize=13, weight='bold', color='white')
    ax.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12, color='white'); ax.set_ylabel("Temperature Anomaly (C)", fontsize=12, color='white')
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', colors='white'); ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white')
    min_lim = np.inf; max_lim = -np.inf
    if any_series_plotted:
         for s in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
              df = anomalies.get(s);
              if df is not None and 'anomaly' in df and df['anomaly'].notna().any(): min_lim=min(min_lim,df['anomaly'].min(skipna=True)); max_lim=max(max_lim,df['anomaly'].max(skipna=True))
         if np.isfinite(min_lim) and np.isfinite(max_lim): ax.set_ylim(min_lim - 0.5, max_lim + 0.5)
         else: ax.set_ylim(-2.5, 3.5)
    else: ax.set_ylim(-2.5, 3.5)
    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3, color='gray'); ax.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.5)
    box = ax.get_position(); ax.set_position([box.x0, box.y0, box.width * 0.75, box.height])
    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels();
    if handles: ax.legend(handles, labels, loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.02, 1), borderaxespad=0., fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white')

    # --- Basemap Inlay ---
    if basemap_available and df_meta_idx is not None:
        stations_to_map = [id for series in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU'] if stations_used.get(series) for id in stations_used[series]]
        stations_to_map = list(set(stations_to_map)) # Unique stations

        if stations_to_map:
             print(f"Adding basemap inlay for {data_type_label} with {len(stations_to_map)} unique stations...")
             try:
                 ax_inset = fig.add_axes([0.78, 0.15, 0.20, 0.20]);
                 m = Basemap(projection='lcc', resolution='l', lat_0=39, lon_0=-96, llcrnrlon=-125, llcrnrlat=23, urcrnrlon=-65, urcrnrlat=50, ax=ax_inset)
                 # *** CORRECTED LINES ***
                 m.drawcoastlines(color='0.6', linewidth=0.5)
                 m.drawcountries(color='0.6', linewidth=0.5)
                 m.drawstates(color='0.5', linewidth=0.5)
                 # *** END CORRECTIONS ***
                 m.fillcontinents(color='0.2', lake_color='0.1'); marker_size = 10
                 # Plot points
                 for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
                     ids = stations_used.get(series_name, [])
                     if ids:
                          coords = df_meta_idx.reindex(ids).dropna(subset=[settings['meta_lat_col'], settings['meta_lon_col']])
                          if not coords.empty:
                               x, y = m(coords[settings['meta_lon_col']].values, coords[settings['meta_lat_col']].values)
                               m.scatter(x, y, s=marker_size, color=colors[series_name], marker=markers[series_name], alpha=0.8, zorder=5+list(colors.keys()).index(series_name))
                 ax_inset.set_title("Station Locations", fontsize=9, color='white')
             except Exception as map_e: print(f"Basemap inlay Error: {map_e}")
        else:
             print(f"Map inlay skipped for {data_type_label}: No stations passed filters.")
    # --- End Basemap Inlay ---
    # Footnote setup
    data_source_filename = f"ghcnm.tavg.latest.{data_type_label.lower()}.dat"; meta_filename = metadata_url.split('/')[-1]
    fig.text(0.01, -0.03, f"Data: US Stations from GHCN v4 ({data_source_filename}) | Metadata: {meta_filename}\nYearly avg >= {settings['min_months']} months/yr | Baseline: {settings['baseline_start']}{settings['baseline_end']} | Coverage: {settings['start_year']}-{settings['end_year']}\nH8: Avg({counts.get('H8', 0)} pairs) | LowBU: Avg(N={counts.get('LowBU', 0)}, {settings['low_bu_min']}-{settings['low_bu_max']}%) | HighBU: Avg(N={counts.get('HighBU', 0)}, >{settings['high_bu_min']}%)", fontsize=8.5, color='white', va='top')
    try: plt.savefig(filename, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Plot saved as {filename}")
    except Exception as e: print(f"\nError saving plot {filename}: {e}")
    plt.show(); plt.close(fig)

output_dir = "ghcn_plots_final_static_v4" # New output dir name
if not os.path.exists(output_dir): os.makedirs(output_dir); print(f"Created output directory: {output_dir}")
raw_data_frames = {}; ghcn_filenames = {}; processed_data = {}
# --- Load Raw Data --- (Unchanged)
print("\n--- Loading Raw Data ---")
for dt_label, dt_info in data_types.items(): raw_data_frames[dt_label], ghcn_filenames[dt_label] = load_and_process_ghcn( dt_info['url'], dt_info['suffix'], all_needed_ids, settings['start_year'], settings['end_year'], settings['min_months'] )
# --- Calculate Anomalies --- (Unchanged - uses corrected function)
print("\n--- Calculating Anomalies ---")
for dt_label, df_raw in raw_data_frames.items():
    if df_raw is not None and not df_raw.empty: processed_data[dt_label] = calculate_anomalies(df_raw, station_id_groups, settings)
    else: print(f"Skipping anomaly calc for {dt_label}."); processed_data[dt_label] = { 'anomalies': {}, 'stations_used': {}, 'counts': {} }
# --- Generate Plots --- (Unchanged)
print("\n--- Generating Plots ---")
if "QCU" in processed_data: plot_anomalies(processed_data["QCU"], "QCU", df_meta_us_indexed, settings, os.path.join(output_dir, "ghcn_us_qcu_anomalies.png"))
if "QCF" in processed_data: plot_anomalies(processed_data["QCF"], "QCF", df_meta_us_indexed, settings, os.path.join(output_dir, "ghcn_us_qcf_anomalies.png"))
if "QCU" in processed_data and "QCF" in processed_data:
    qcu_ok = any(processed_data["QCU"]['counts'].get(s, 0) > 0 for s in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU'])
    qcf_ok = any(processed_data["QCF"]['counts'].get(s, 0) > 0 for s in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU'])
    raw_qcu_ok = raw_data_frames.get("QCU") is not None and not raw_data_frames["QCU"].empty
    raw_qcf_ok = raw_data_frames.get("QCF") is not None and not raw_data_frames["QCF"].empty
    if qcu_ok and qcf_ok:
        plot_comparison( processed_data["QCU"], processed_data["QCF"], settings, os.path.join(output_dir, "ghcn_us_qcu_vs_qcf_comparison.png") )
        if raw_qcu_ok and raw_qcf_ok: plot_difference( raw_data_frames["QCU"], raw_data_frames["QCF"], processed_data["QCU"], processed_data["QCF"], settings, os.path.join(output_dir, "ghcn_us_qcf_minus_qcu_difference.png") )
        else: print("\nSkipping difference plot: Missing raw data.")
    else: print("\nSkipping comparison/difference plots: Missing anomaly results.")
else: print("\nSkipping comparison/difference plots: Missing processed data.")

print("\n--- Script Finished ---")
